58bool PayloadTypeSupportsSkippingFecPackets(const std::string& payload_name,
59 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
60 const VideoCodecType codecType = PayloadStringToCodecType(payload_name);
61 if (codecType == kVideoCodecVP8 || codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
62 return true;
63 }
64 if (codecType == kVideoCodecGeneric &&
65 absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup("WebRTC-GenericPictureId"), "Enabled")) {
66 return true;
67 }
68 return false;
69}
70
71bool ShouldDisableRedAndUlpfec(bool flexfec_enabled,
72 const RtpConfig& rtp_config,
73 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
74 // Consistency of NACK and RED+ULPFEC parameters is checked in this function.
75 const bool nack_enabled = rtp_config.nack.rtp_history_ms > 0;
76
77 // Shorthands.
78 auto IsRedEnabled = [&]() { return rtp_config.ulpfec.red_payload_type >= 0; };
79 auto IsUlpfecEnabled = [&]() {
80 return rtp_config.ulpfec.ulpfec_payload_type >= 0;
81 };
82
83 bool should_disable_red_and_ulpfec = false;
84
85 if (absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup("WebRTC-DisableUlpFecExperiment"),
86 "Enabled")) {
87 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Experiment to disable sending ULPFEC is enabled.";
88 should_disable_red_and_ulpfec = true;
89 }
90
91 // If enabled, FlexFEC takes priority over RED+ULPFEC.
92 if (flexfec_enabled) {
93 if (IsUlpfecEnabled()) {
94 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
95 << "Both FlexFEC and ULPFEC are configured. Disabling ULPFEC.";
96 }
97 should_disable_red_and_ulpfec = true;
98 }
99
100 // Payload types without picture ID cannot determine that a stream is complete
101 // without retransmitting FEC, so using ULPFEC + NACK for H.264 (for instance)
102 // is a waste of bandwidth since FEC packets still have to be transmitted.
103 // Note that this is not the case with FlexFEC.
104 if (nack_enabled && IsUlpfecEnabled() &&
105 !PayloadTypeSupportsSkippingFecPackets(rtp_config.payload_name, trials)) {
106 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
107 << "Transmitting payload type without picture ID using "
108 "NACK+ULPFEC is a waste of bandwidth since ULPFEC packets "
109 "also have to be retransmitted. Disabling ULPFEC.";
110 should_disable_red_and_ulpfec = true;
111 }
112
113 // Verify payload types.
114 if (IsUlpfecEnabled() ^ IsRedEnabled()) {
115 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
116 << "Only RED or only ULPFEC enabled, but not both. Disabling both.";
117 should_disable_red_and_ulpfec = true;
118 }
119
120 return should_disable_red_and_ulpfec;
121}
122
123// TODO(brandtr): Update this function when we support multistream protection.
124std::unique_ptr<VideoFecGenerator> MaybeCreateFecGenerator(
125 Clock* clock,
126 const RtpConfig& rtp,
127 const std::map<uint32_t, RtpState>& suspended_ssrcs,
128 int simulcast_index,
129 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
130 // If flexfec is configured that takes priority.
131 if (rtp.flexfec.payload_type >= 0) {
132 RTC_DCHECK_GE(rtp.flexfec.payload_type, 0);
133 RTC_DCHECK_LE(rtp.flexfec.payload_type, 127);
134 if (rtp.flexfec.ssrc == 0) {
135 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "FlexFEC is enabled, but no FlexFEC SSRC given. "
136 "Therefore disabling FlexFEC.";
137 return nullptr;
138 }
139 if (rtp.flexfec.protected_media_ssrcs.empty()) {
140 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
141 << "FlexFEC is enabled, but no protected media SSRC given. "
142 "Therefore disabling FlexFEC.";
143 return nullptr;
144 }
145
146 if (rtp.flexfec.protected_media_ssrcs.size() > 1) {
147 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
148 << "The supplied FlexfecConfig contained multiple protected "
149 "media streams, but our implementation currently only "
150 "supports protecting a single media stream. "
151 "To avoid confusion, disabling FlexFEC completely.";
152 return nullptr;
153 }
154
155 if (absl::c_find(rtp.flexfec.protected_media_ssrcs,
156 rtp.ssrcs[simulcast_index]) ==
157 rtp.flexfec.protected_media_ssrcs.end()) {
158 // Media SSRC not among flexfec protected SSRCs.
159 return nullptr;
160 }
161
162 const RtpState* rtp_state = nullptr;
163 auto it = suspended_ssrcs.find(rtp.flexfec.ssrc);
164 if (it != suspended_ssrcs.end()) {
165 rtp_state = &it->second;
166 }
167
168 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(1U, rtp.flexfec.protected_media_ssrcs.size());
169 return std::make_unique<FlexfecSender>(
170 rtp.flexfec.payload_type, rtp.flexfec.ssrc,
171 rtp.flexfec.protected_media_ssrcs[0], rtp.mid, rtp.extensions,
172 RTPSender::FecExtensionSizes(), rtp_state, clock);
173 } else if (rtp.ulpfec.red_payload_type >= 0 &&
174 rtp.ulpfec.ulpfec_payload_type >= 0 &&
175 !ShouldDisableRedAndUlpfec(/*flexfec_enabled=*/false, rtp,
176 trials)) {
177 // Flexfec not configured, but ulpfec is and is not disabled.
178 return std::make_unique<UlpfecGenerator>(
179 rtp.ulpfec.red_payload_type, rtp.ulpfec.ulpfec_payload_type, clock);
180 }
181
182 // Not a single FEC is given.
183 return nullptr;
184}

186std::vector<RtpStreamSender> CreateRtpStreamSenders(
187 Clock* clock,
188 const RtpConfig& rtp_config,
189 const RtpSenderObservers& observers,
190 int rtcp_report_interval_ms,
191 Transport* send_transport,
192 RtcpBandwidthObserver* bandwidth_callback,
193 RtpTransportControllerSendInterface* transport,
194 const std::map<uint32_t, RtpState>& suspended_ssrcs,
195 RtcEventLog* event_log,
196 RateLimiter* retransmission_rate_limiter,
197 FrameEncryptorInterface* frame_encryptor,
198 const CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
199 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer,
200 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
201 RTC_DCHECK_GT(rtp_config.ssrcs.size(), 0);
202
203 RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration configuration;
204 configuration.clock = clock;
205 configuration.audio = false;
206 configuration.receiver_only = false;
207 configuration.outgoing_transport = send_transport;
208 configuration.intra_frame_callback = observers.intra_frame_callback;
209 configuration.rtcp_loss_notification_observer =
210 observers.rtcp_loss_notification_observer;
211 configuration.bandwidth_callback = bandwidth_callback;
212 configuration.network_state_estimate_observer =
213 transport->network_state_estimate_observer();
214 configuration.transport_feedback_callback =
215 transport->transport_feedback_observer();
216 configuration.rtt_stats = observers.rtcp_rtt_stats;
217 configuration.rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer =
218 observers.rtcp_type_observer;
219 configuration.report_block_data_observer =
220 observers.report_block_data_observer;
221 configuration.paced_sender = transport->packet_sender();
222 configuration.send_bitrate_observer = observers.bitrate_observer;
223 configuration.send_side_delay_observer = observers.send_delay_observer;
224 configuration.send_packet_observer = observers.send_packet_observer;
225 configuration.event_log = event_log;
226 configuration.retransmission_rate_limiter = retransmission_rate_limiter;
227 configuration.rtp_stats_callback = observers.rtp_stats;
228 configuration.frame_encryptor = frame_encryptor;
229 configuration.require_frame_encryption =
230 crypto_options.sframe.require_frame_encryption;
231 configuration.extmap_allow_mixed = rtp_config.extmap_allow_mixed;
232 configuration.rtcp_report_interval_ms = rtcp_report_interval_ms;
233 configuration.field_trials = &trials;
234
235 std::vector<RtpStreamSender> rtp_streams;
236
237 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_config.rtx.ssrcs.empty() ||
238 rtp_config.rtx.ssrcs.size() == rtp_config.ssrcs.size());
239 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_config.ssrcs.size(); ++i) {
240 RTPSenderVideo::Config video_config;
241 configuration.local_media_ssrc = rtp_config.ssrcs[i];
242
243 std::unique_ptr<VideoFecGenerator> fec_generator =
244 MaybeCreateFecGenerator(clock, rtp_config, suspended_ssrcs, i, trials);
245 configuration.fec_generator = fec_generator.get();
246
247 configuration.rtx_send_ssrc =
248 rtp_config.GetRtxSsrcAssociatedWithMediaSsrc(rtp_config.ssrcs[i]);
249 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(configuration.rtx_send_ssrc.has_value(),
250 !rtp_config.rtx.ssrcs.empty());
251
252 configuration.need_rtp_packet_infos = rtp_config.lntf.enabled;
253
254 std::unique_ptr<ModuleRtpRtcpImpl2> rtp_rtcp(
255 ModuleRtpRtcpImpl2::Create(configuration));
256 rtp_rtcp->SetSendingStatus(false);
257 rtp_rtcp->SetSendingMediaStatus(false);
258 rtp_rtcp->SetRTCPStatus(RtcpMode::kCompound);
259 // Set NACK.
260 rtp_rtcp->SetStorePacketsStatus(true, kMinSendSidePacketHistorySize);
261
262 video_config.clock = configuration.clock;
263 video_config.rtp_sender = rtp_rtcp->RtpSender();
264 video_config.frame_encryptor = frame_encryptor;
265 video_config.require_frame_encryption =
266 crypto_options.sframe.require_frame_encryption;
267 video_config.enable_retransmit_all_layers = false;
268 video_config.field_trials = &trials;
269
270 const bool using_flexfec =
271 fec_generator &&
272 fec_generator->GetFecType() == VideoFecGenerator::FecType::kFlexFec;
273 const bool should_disable_red_and_ulpfec =
274 ShouldDisableRedAndUlpfec(using_flexfec, rtp_config, trials);
275 if (!should_disable_red_and_ulpfec &&
276 rtp_config.ulpfec.red_payload_type != -1) {
277 video_config.red_payload_type = rtp_config.ulpfec.red_payload_type;
278 }
279 if (fec_generator) {
280 video_config.fec_type = fec_generator->GetFecType();
281 video_config.fec_overhead_bytes = fec_generator->MaxPacketOverhead();
282 }
283 video_config.frame_transformer = frame_transformer;
284 video_config.send_transport_queue = transport->GetWorkerQueue()->Get();
285 auto sender_video = std::make_unique<RTPSenderVideo>(video_config);
286 rtp_streams.emplace_back(std::move(rtp_rtcp), std::move(sender_video),
287 std::move(fec_generator));
288 }
289 return rtp_streams;
290}
291
292absl::optional<VideoCodecType> GetVideoCodecType(const RtpConfig& config) {
293 if (config.raw_payload) {
294 return absl::nullopt;
295 }
296 return PayloadStringToCodecType(config.payload_name);
297}
298bool TransportSeqNumExtensionConfigured(const RtpConfig& config) {
299 return absl::c_any_of(config.extensions, [](const RtpExtension& ext) {
300 return ext.uri == RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberUri;
301 });
302}
303
304// Returns true when some coded video sequence can be decoded starting with
305// this frame without requiring any previous frames.
306// e.g. it is the same as a key frame when spatial scalability is not used.
307// When spatial scalability is used, then it is true for layer frames of
308// a key frame without inter-layer dependencies.
309bool IsFirstFrameOfACodedVideoSequence(
310 const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
311 const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_specific_info) {
312 if (encoded_image._frameType != VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
313 return false;
314 }
315
316 if (codec_specific_info != nullptr) {
317 if (codec_specific_info->generic_frame_info.has_value()) {
318 // This function is used before
319 // `codec_specific_info->generic_frame_info->frame_diffs` are calculated,
320 // so need to use a more complicated way to check for presence of the
321 // dependencies.
322 return absl::c_none_of(
323 codec_specific_info->generic_frame_info->encoder_buffers,
324 [](const CodecBufferUsage& buffer) { return buffer.referenced; });
325 }
326
327 if (codec_specific_info->codecType == VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecVP8 ||
328 codec_specific_info->codecType == VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecH264 ||
329 codec_specific_info->codecType == VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecGeneric) {
330 // These codecs do not support intra picture dependencies, so a frame
331 // marked as a key frame should be a key frame.
332 return true;
333 }
334 }
335
336 // Without depenedencies described in generic format do an educated guess.
337 // It might be wrong for VP9 with spatial layer 0 skipped or higher spatial
338 // layer not depending on the spatial layer 0. This corner case is unimportant
339 // for current usage of this helper function.
340
341 // Use <= to accept both 0 (i.e. the first) and nullopt (i.e. the only).
342 return encoded_image.SpatialIndex() <= 0;
343}

347RtpVideoSender::RtpVideoSender(
348 Clock* clock,
349 std::map<uint32_t, RtpState> suspended_ssrcs,
350 const std::map<uint32_t, RtpPayloadState>& states,
351 const RtpConfig& rtp_config,
352 int rtcp_report_interval_ms,
353 Transport* send_transport,
354 const RtpSenderObservers& observers,
355 RtpTransportControllerSendInterface* transport,
356 RtcEventLog* event_log,
357 RateLimiter* retransmission_limiter,
358 std::unique_ptr<FecController> fec_controller,
359 FrameEncryptorInterface* frame_encryptor,
360 const CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
361 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer)
362 : send_side_bwe_with_overhead_(!absl::StartsWith(
363 field_trials_.Lookup("WebRTC-SendSideBwe-WithOverhead"),
364 "Disabled")),
365 use_frame_rate_for_overhead_(absl::StartsWith(
366 field_trials_.Lookup("WebRTC-Video-UseFrameRateForOverhead"),
367 "Enabled")),
368 has_packet_feedback_(TransportSeqNumExtensionConfigured(rtp_config)),
369 simulate_vp9_structure_(absl::StartsWith(
370 field_trials_.Lookup("WebRTC-Vp9DependencyDescriptor"),
371 "Enabled")),
372 active_(false),
373 module_process_thread_(nullptr),
374 suspended_ssrcs_(std::move(suspended_ssrcs)),
375 fec_controller_(std::move(fec_controller)),
376 fec_allowed_(true),
377 rtp_streams_(CreateRtpStreamSenders(clock,
378 rtp_config,
379 observers,
380 rtcp_report_interval_ms,
381 send_transport,
382 transport->GetBandwidthObserver(),
383 transport,
384 suspended_ssrcs_,
385 event_log,
386 retransmission_limiter,
387 frame_encryptor,
388 crypto_options,
389 std::move(frame_transformer),
390 field_trials_)),
391 rtp_config_(rtp_config),
392 codec_type_(GetVideoCodecType(rtp_config)),
393 transport_(transport),
394 transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_(0),
395 encoder_target_rate_bps_(0),
396 frame_counts_(rtp_config.ssrcs.size()),
397 frame_count_observer_(observers.frame_count_observer) {
398 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(rtp_config_.ssrcs.size(), rtp_streams_.size());
399 if (send_side_bwe_with_overhead_ && has_packet_feedback_)
400 transport_->IncludeOverheadInPacedSender();
401 module_process_thread_checker_.Detach();
402 // SSRCs are assumed to be sorted in the same order as |rtp_modules|.
403 for (uint32_t ssrc : rtp_config_.ssrcs) {
404 // Restore state if it previously existed.
405 const RtpPayloadState* state = nullptr;
406 auto it = states.find(ssrc);
407 if (it != states.end()) {
408 state = &it->second;
409 shared_frame_id_ = std::max(shared_frame_id_, state->shared_frame_id);
410 }
411 params_.push_back(RtpPayloadParams(ssrc, state, field_trials_));
412 }
413
414 // RTP/RTCP initialization.
415
416 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_config_.extensions.size(); ++i) {
417 const std::string& extension = rtp_config_.extensions[i].uri;
418 int id = rtp_config_.extensions[i].id;
419 RTC_DCHECK(RtpExtension::IsSupportedForVideo(extension));
420 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
421 stream.rtp_rtcp->RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(extension, id);
422 }
423 }
424
425 ConfigureSsrcs();
426 ConfigureRids();
427
428 if (!rtp_config_.mid.empty()) {
429 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
430 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetMid(rtp_config_.mid);
431 }
432 }
433
434 bool fec_enabled = false;
435 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
436 // Simulcast has one module for each layer. Set the CNAME on all modules.
437 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetCNAME(rtp_config_.c_name.c_str());
438 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetMaxRtpPacketSize(rtp_config_.max_packet_size);
439 stream.rtp_rtcp->RegisterSendPayloadFrequency(rtp_config_.payload_type,
440 kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency);
441 if (stream.fec_generator != nullptr) {
442 fec_enabled = true;
443 }
444 }
445 // Currently, both ULPFEC and FlexFEC use the same FEC rate calculation logic,
446 // so enable that logic if either of those FEC schemes are enabled.
447 fec_controller_->SetProtectionMethod(fec_enabled, NackEnabled());
448
449 fec_controller_->SetProtectionCallback(this);
450 // Signal congestion controller this object is ready for OnPacket* callbacks.
451 transport_->GetStreamFeedbackProvider()->RegisterStreamFeedbackObserver(
452 rtp_config_.ssrcs, this);
453}
454
455RtpVideoSender::~RtpVideoSender() {
456 SetActiveModulesLocked(
457 std::vector<bool>(rtp_streams_.size(), /*active=*/false));
458 transport_->GetStreamFeedbackProvider()->DeRegisterStreamFeedbackObserver(
459 this);
460}
461
462void RtpVideoSender::RegisterProcessThread(
463 ProcessThread* module_process_thread) {
464 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&module_process_thread_checker_);
465 RTC_DCHECK(!module_process_thread_);
466 module_process_thread_ = module_process_thread;
467
468 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
469 module_process_thread_->RegisterModule(stream.rtp_rtcp.get(),
470 RTC_FROM_HERE);
471 }
472}
473
474void RtpVideoSender::DeRegisterProcessThread() {
475 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&module_process_thread_checker_);
476 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_)
477 module_process_thread_->DeRegisterModule(stream.rtp_rtcp.get());
478}
479
480void RtpVideoSender::SetActive(bool active) {
481 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
482 if (active_ == active)
483 return;
484 const std::vector<bool> active_modules(rtp_streams_.size(), active);
485 SetActiveModulesLocked(active_modules);
486}
487
488void RtpVideoSender::SetActiveModules(const std::vector<bool> active_modules) {
489 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
490 return SetActiveModulesLocked(active_modules);
491}
492
493void RtpVideoSender::SetActiveModulesLocked(
494 const std::vector<bool> active_modules) {
495 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(rtp_streams_.size(), active_modules.size());
496 active_ = false;
497 for (size_t i = 0; i < active_modules.size(); ++i) {
498 if (active_modules[i]) {
499 active_ = true;
500 }
501
502 RtpRtcpInterface& rtp_module = *rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp;
503 const bool was_active = rtp_module.SendingMedia();
504 const bool should_be_active = active_modules[i];
505
506 // Sends a kRtcpByeCode when going from true to false.
507 rtp_module.SetSendingStatus(active_modules[i]);
508
509 if (was_active && !should_be_active) {
510 // Disabling media, remove from packet router map to reduce size and
511 // prevent any stray packets in the pacer from asynchronously arriving
512 // to a disabled module.
513 transport_->packet_router()->RemoveSendRtpModule(&rtp_module);
514 }
515
516 // If set to false this module won't send media.
517 rtp_module.SetSendingMediaStatus(active_modules[i]);
518
519 if (!was_active && should_be_active) {
520 // Turning on media, register with packet router.
521 transport_->packet_router()->AddSendRtpModule(&rtp_module,
522 /*remb_candidate=*/true);
523 }
524 }
525}
526
527bool RtpVideoSender::IsActive() {
528 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
529 return IsActiveLocked();
530}
531
532bool RtpVideoSender::IsActiveLocked() {
533 return active_ && !rtp_streams_.empty();
534}
535
536EncodedImageCallback::Result RtpVideoSender::OnEncodedImage(
537 const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
538 const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_specific_info) {
539 fec_controller_->UpdateWithEncodedData(encoded_image.size(),
540 encoded_image._frameType);
541 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
542 RTC_DCHECK(!rtp_streams_.empty());
543 if (!active_)
544 return Result(Result::ERROR_SEND_FAILED);
545
546 shared_frame_id_++;
547 size_t stream_index = 0;
548 if (codec_specific_info &&
549 (codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP8 ||
550 codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecH264 ||
551 codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecGeneric)) {
552 // Map spatial index to simulcast.
553 stream_index = encoded_image.SpatialIndex().value_or(0);
554 }
555 RTC_DCHECK_LT(stream_index, rtp_streams_.size());
556
557 uint32_t rtp_timestamp =
558 encoded_image.Timestamp() +
559 rtp_streams_[stream_index].rtp_rtcp->StartTimestamp();
560
561 // RTCPSender has it's own copy of the timestamp offset, added in
562 // RTCPSender::BuildSR, hence we must not add the in the offset for this call.
563 // TODO(nisse): Delete RTCPSender:timestamp_offset_, and see if we can confine
564 // knowledge of the offset to a single place.
565 if (!rtp_streams_[stream_index].rtp_rtcp->OnSendingRtpFrame(
566 encoded_image.Timestamp(), encoded_image.capture_time_ms_,
567 rtp_config_.payload_type,
568 encoded_image._frameType == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey)) {
569 // The payload router could be active but this module isn't sending.
570 return Result(Result::ERROR_SEND_FAILED);
571 }
572
573 absl::optional<int64_t> expected_retransmission_time_ms;
574 if (encoded_image.RetransmissionAllowed()) {
575 expected_retransmission_time_ms =
576 rtp_streams_[stream_index].rtp_rtcp->ExpectedRetransmissionTimeMs();
577 }
578
579 if (IsFirstFrameOfACodedVideoSequence(encoded_image, codec_specific_info)) {
580 // If encoder adapter produce FrameDependencyStructure, pass it so that
581 // dependency descriptor rtp header extension can be used.
582 // If not supported, disable using dependency descriptor by passing nullptr.
583 RTPSenderVideo& sender_video = *rtp_streams_[stream_index].sender_video;
584 if (codec_specific_info && codec_specific_info->template_structure) {
585 sender_video.SetVideoStructure(&*codec_specific_info->template_structure);
586 } else if (simulate_vp9_structure_ && codec_specific_info &&
587 codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
588 FrameDependencyStructure structure =
589 RtpPayloadParams::MinimalisticVp9Structure(
590 codec_specific_info->codecSpecific.VP9);
591 sender_video.SetVideoStructure(&structure);
592 } else {
593 sender_video.SetVideoStructure(nullptr);
594 }
595 }
596
597 bool send_result = rtp_streams_[stream_index].sender_video->SendEncodedImage(
598 rtp_config_.payload_type, codec_type_, rtp_timestamp, encoded_image,
599 params_[stream_index].GetRtpVideoHeader(
600 encoded_image, codec_specific_info, shared_frame_id_),
601 expected_retransmission_time_ms);
602 if (frame_count_observer_) {
603 FrameCounts& counts = frame_counts_[stream_index];
604 if (encoded_image._frameType == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
605 ++counts.key_frames;
606 } else if (encoded_image._frameType == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta) {
607 ++counts.delta_frames;
608 } else {
609 RTC_DCHECK(encoded_image._frameType == VideoFrameType::kEmptyFrame);
610 }
611 frame_count_observer_->FrameCountUpdated(counts,
612 rtp_config_.ssrcs[stream_index]);
613 }
614 if (!send_result)
615 return Result(Result::ERROR_SEND_FAILED);
616
617 return Result(Result::OK, rtp_timestamp);
618}
619
620void RtpVideoSender::OnBitrateAllocationUpdated(
621 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate) {
622 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
623 if (IsActiveLocked()) {
624 if (rtp_streams_.size() == 1) {
625 // If spatial scalability is enabled, it is covered by a single stream.
626 rtp_streams_[0].rtp_rtcp->SetVideoBitrateAllocation(bitrate);
627 } else {
628 std::vector<absl::optional<VideoBitrateAllocation>> layer_bitrates =
629 bitrate.GetSimulcastAllocations();
630 // Simulcast is in use, split the VideoBitrateAllocation into one struct
631 // per rtp stream, moving over the temporal layer allocation.
632 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_streams_.size(); ++i) {
633 // The next spatial layer could be used if the current one is
634 // inactive.
635 if (layer_bitrates[i]) {
636 rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp->SetVideoBitrateAllocation(
637 *layer_bitrates[i]);
638 } else {
639 // Signal a 0 bitrate on a simulcast stream.
640 rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp->SetVideoBitrateAllocation(
641 VideoBitrateAllocation());
642 }
643 }
644 }
645 }
646}
647void RtpVideoSender::OnVideoLayersAllocationUpdated(
648 const VideoLayersAllocation& allocation) {
649 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
650 if (IsActiveLocked()) {
651 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_streams_.size(); ++i) {
652 VideoLayersAllocation stream_allocation = allocation;
653 stream_allocation.rtp_stream_index = i;
654 rtp_streams_[i].sender_video->SetVideoLayersAllocation(
655 std::move(stream_allocation));
656 }
657 }
658}

666 uint32_t packetization_overhead_bps = 0;
667 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_streams_.size(); ++i) {

682void RtpVideoSender::ConfigureSsrcs() {
683 // Configure regular SSRCs.
684 RTC_CHECK(ssrc_to_rtp_module_.empty());
685 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_config_.ssrcs.size(); ++i) {
686 uint32_t ssrc = rtp_config_.ssrcs[i];
687 RtpRtcpInterface* const rtp_rtcp = rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp.get();
688
689 // Restore RTP state if previous existed.
690 auto it = suspended_ssrcs_.find(ssrc);
691 if (it != suspended_ssrcs_.end())
692 rtp_rtcp->SetRtpState(it->second);
693
694 ssrc_to_rtp_module_[ssrc] = rtp_rtcp;
695 }
696
697 // Set up RTX if available.
698 if (rtp_config_.rtx.ssrcs.empty())
699 return;
700
701 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(rtp_config_.rtx.ssrcs.size(), rtp_config_.ssrcs.size());
702 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_config_.rtx.ssrcs.size(); ++i) {
703 uint32_t ssrc = rtp_config_.rtx.ssrcs[i];
704 RtpRtcpInterface* const rtp_rtcp = rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp.get();
705 auto it = suspended_ssrcs_.find(ssrc);
706 if (it != suspended_ssrcs_.end())
707 rtp_rtcp->SetRtxState(it->second);
708 }
709
710 // Configure RTX payload types.
711 RTC_DCHECK_GE(rtp_config_.rtx.payload_type, 0);
712 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
713 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetRtxSendPayloadType(rtp_config_.rtx.payload_type,
714 rtp_config_.payload_type);
715 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetRtxSendStatus(kRtxRetransmitted |
716 kRtxRedundantPayloads);
717 }
718 if (rtp_config_.ulpfec.red_payload_type != -1 &&
719 rtp_config_.ulpfec.red_rtx_payload_type != -1) {
720 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
721 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetRtxSendPayloadType(
722 rtp_config_.ulpfec.red_rtx_payload_type,
723 rtp_config_.ulpfec.red_payload_type);
724 }
725 }
726}
727
728void RtpVideoSender::ConfigureRids() {
729 if (rtp_config_.rids.empty())
730 return;
731
732 // Some streams could have been disabled, but the rids are still there.
733 // This will occur when simulcast has been disabled for a codec (e.g. VP9)
734 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_config_.rids.size() >= rtp_streams_.size());
735 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_streams_.size(); ++i) {
736 rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp->SetRid(rtp_config_.rids[i]);
737 }
738}

740void RtpVideoSender::OnNetworkAvailability(bool network_available) {
741 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
742 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetRTCPStatus(network_available ? rtp_config_.rtcp_mode
743 : RtcpMode::kOff);
744 }

747std::map<uint32_t, RtpState> RtpVideoSender::GetRtpStates() const {
748 std::map<uint32_t, RtpState> rtp_states;
749
750 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_config_.ssrcs.size(); ++i) {
751 uint32_t ssrc = rtp_config_.ssrcs[i];
752 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(ssrc, rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp->SSRC());
753 rtp_states[ssrc] = rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp->GetRtpState();
754
755 // Only happens during shutdown, when RTP module is already inactive,
756 // so OK to call fec generator here.
757 if (rtp_streams_[i].fec_generator) {
758 absl::optional<RtpState> fec_state =
759 rtp_streams_[i].fec_generator->GetRtpState();
760 if (fec_state) {
761 uint32_t ssrc = rtp_config_.flexfec.ssrc;
762 rtp_states[ssrc] = *fec_state;
763 }
764 }
765 }
766
767 for (size_t i = 0; i < rtp_config_.rtx.ssrcs.size(); ++i) {
768 uint32_t ssrc = rtp_config_.rtx.ssrcs[i];
769 rtp_states[ssrc] = rtp_streams_[i].rtp_rtcp->GetRtxState();
770 }
771
772 return rtp_states;
773}
774
775std::map<uint32_t, RtpPayloadState> RtpVideoSender::GetRtpPayloadStates()
776 const {
777 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
778 std::map<uint32_t, RtpPayloadState> payload_states;
779 for (const auto& param : params_) {
780 payload_states[param.ssrc()] = param.state();
781 payload_states[param.ssrc()].shared_frame_id = shared_frame_id_;
782 }
783 return payload_states;
784}

786void RtpVideoSender::OnTransportOverheadChanged(
787 size_t transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet) {
788 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
789 transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_ = transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet;
790
791 size_t max_rtp_packet_size =
792 std::min(rtp_config_.max_packet_size,
793 kPathMTU - transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_);
794 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
795 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetMaxRtpPacketSize(max_rtp_packet_size);
796 }
797}
798
799void RtpVideoSender::OnBitrateUpdated(BitrateAllocationUpdate update,
800 int framerate) {
801 // Substract overhead from bitrate.
802 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
803 size_t num_active_streams = 0;
804 size_t overhead_bytes_per_packet = 0;
805 for (const auto& stream : rtp_streams_) {
806 if (stream.rtp_rtcp->SendingMedia()) {
807 overhead_bytes_per_packet += stream.rtp_rtcp->ExpectedPerPacketOverhead();
808 ++num_active_streams;
809 }
810 }
811 if (num_active_streams > 1) {
812 overhead_bytes_per_packet /= num_active_streams;
813 }
814
815 DataSize packet_overhead = DataSize::Bytes(
816 overhead_bytes_per_packet + transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_);
817 DataSize max_total_packet_size = DataSize::Bytes(
818 rtp_config_.max_packet_size + transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_);
819 uint32_t payload_bitrate_bps = update.target_bitrate.bps();
820 if (send_side_bwe_with_overhead_ && has_packet_feedback_) {
821 DataRate overhead_rate =
822 CalculateOverheadRate(update.target_bitrate, max_total_packet_size,
823 packet_overhead, Frequency::Hertz(framerate));
824 // TODO(srte): We probably should not accept 0 payload bitrate here.
825 payload_bitrate_bps = rtc::saturated_cast<uint32_t>(payload_bitrate_bps -
826 overhead_rate.bps());
827 }
828
829 // Get the encoder target rate. It is the estimated network rate -
830 // protection overhead.
831 // TODO(srte): We should multiply with 255 here.
832 encoder_target_rate_bps_ = fec_controller_->UpdateFecRates(
833 payload_bitrate_bps, framerate,
834 rtc::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(update.packet_loss_ratio * 256),
835 loss_mask_vector_, update.round_trip_time.ms());
836 if (!fec_allowed_) {
837 encoder_target_rate_bps_ = payload_bitrate_bps;
838 // fec_controller_->UpdateFecRates() was still called so as to allow
839 // |fec_controller_| to update whatever internal state it might have,
840 // since |fec_allowed_| may be toggled back on at any moment.
841 }
842
843 // Subtract packetization overhead from the encoder target. If target rate
844 // is really low, cap the overhead at 50%. This also avoids the case where
845 // |encoder_target_rate_bps_| is 0 due to encoder pause event while the
846 // packetization rate is positive since packets are still flowing.
847 uint32_t packetization_rate_bps =
848 std::min(GetPacketizationOverheadRate(), encoder_target_rate_bps_ / 2);
849 encoder_target_rate_bps_ -= packetization_rate_bps;
850
851 loss_mask_vector_.clear();
852
853 uint32_t encoder_overhead_rate_bps = 0;
854 if (send_side_bwe_with_overhead_ && has_packet_feedback_) {
855 // TODO(srte): The packet size should probably be the same as in the
856 // CalculateOverheadRate call above (just max_total_packet_size), it doesn't
857 // make sense to use different packet rates for different overhead
858 // calculations.
859 DataRate encoder_overhead_rate = CalculateOverheadRate(
860 DataRate::BitsPerSec(encoder_target_rate_bps_),
861 max_total_packet_size - DataSize::Bytes(overhead_bytes_per_packet),
862 packet_overhead, Frequency::Hertz(framerate));
863 encoder_overhead_rate_bps = std::min(
864 encoder_overhead_rate.bps<uint32_t>(),
865 update.target_bitrate.bps<uint32_t>() - encoder_target_rate_bps_);
866 }
867 // When the field trial "WebRTC-SendSideBwe-WithOverhead" is enabled
868 // protection_bitrate includes overhead.
869 const uint32_t media_rate = encoder_target_rate_bps_ +
870 encoder_overhead_rate_bps +
871 packetization_rate_bps;
872 RTC_DCHECK_GE(update.target_bitrate, DataRate::BitsPerSec(media_rate));
873 protection_bitrate_bps_ = update.target_bitrate.bps() - media_rate;
874}
875
876uint32_t RtpVideoSender::GetPayloadBitrateBps() const {
877 return encoder_target_rate_bps_;
878}
879
880uint32_t RtpVideoSender::GetProtectionBitrateBps() const {
881 return protection_bitrate_bps_;
882}

884std::vector<RtpSequenceNumberMap::Info> RtpVideoSender::GetSentRtpPacketInfos(
885 uint32_t ssrc,
886 rtc::ArrayView<const uint16_t> sequence_numbers) const {
887 for (const auto& rtp_stream : rtp_streams_) {
888 if (ssrc == rtp_stream.rtp_rtcp->SSRC()) {
889 return rtp_stream.rtp_rtcp->GetSentRtpPacketInfos(sequence_numbers);
890 }
891 }

894
895int RtpVideoSender::ProtectionRequest(const FecProtectionParams* delta_params,
896 const FecProtectionParams* key_params,
897 uint32_t* sent_video_rate_bps,
898 uint32_t* sent_nack_rate_bps,
899 uint32_t* sent_fec_rate_bps) {
900 *sent_video_rate_bps = 0;
901 *sent_nack_rate_bps = 0;
902 *sent_fec_rate_bps = 0;
903 for (const RtpStreamSender& stream : rtp_streams_) {
904 stream.rtp_rtcp->SetFecProtectionParams(*delta_params, *key_params);
905
906 auto send_bitrate = stream.rtp_rtcp->GetSendRates();
907 *sent_video_rate_bps += send_bitrate[RtpPacketMediaType::kVideo].bps();
908 *sent_fec_rate_bps +=
909 send_bitrate[RtpPacketMediaType::kForwardErrorCorrection].bps();
910 *sent_nack_rate_bps +=
911 send_bitrate[RtpPacketMediaType::kRetransmission].bps();
912 }
913 return 0;
914}

920
921void RtpVideoSender::OnPacketFeedbackVector(
922 std::vector<StreamPacketInfo> packet_feedback_vector) {
923 if (fec_controller_->UseLossVectorMask()) {
924 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
925 for (const StreamPacketInfo& packet : packet_feedback_vector) {
926 loss_mask_vector_.push_back(!packet.received);
927 }
928 }
929
930 // Map from SSRC to all acked packets for that RTP module.
931 std::map<uint32_t, std::vector<uint16_t>> acked_packets_per_ssrc;
932 for (const StreamPacketInfo& packet : packet_feedback_vector) {
933 if (packet.received) {
934 acked_packets_per_ssrc[packet.ssrc].push_back(packet.rtp_sequence_number);
935 }
936 }
937
938 // Map from SSRC to vector of RTP sequence numbers that are indicated as
939 // lost by feedback, without being trailed by any received packets.
940 std::map<uint32_t, std::vector<uint16_t>> early_loss_detected_per_ssrc;
941
942 for (const StreamPacketInfo& packet : packet_feedback_vector) {
943 if (!packet.received) {
944 // Last known lost packet, might not be detectable as lost by remote
945 // jitter buffer.
946 early_loss_detected_per_ssrc[packet.ssrc].push_back(
947 packet.rtp_sequence_number);
948 } else {
949 // Packet received, so any loss prior to this is already detectable.
950 early_loss_detected_per_ssrc.erase(packet.ssrc);
951 }
952 }
953
954 for (const auto& kv : early_loss_detected_per_ssrc) {
955 const uint32_t ssrc = kv.first;
956 auto it = ssrc_to_rtp_module_.find(ssrc);
957 RTC_DCHECK(it != ssrc_to_rtp_module_.end());
958 RTPSender* rtp_sender = it->second->RtpSender();
959 for (uint16_t sequence_number : kv.second) {
960 rtp_sender->ReSendPacket(sequence_number);
961 }
962 }
963
964 for (const auto& kv : acked_packets_per_ssrc) {
965 const uint32_t ssrc = kv.first;
966 auto it = ssrc_to_rtp_module_.find(ssrc);
967 if (it == ssrc_to_rtp_module_.end()) {
968 // Packets not for a media SSRC, so likely RTX or FEC. If so, ignore
969 // since there's no RTP history to clean up anyway.
970 continue;
971 }
972 rtc::ArrayView<const uint16_t> rtp_sequence_numbers(kv.second);
973 it->second->OnPacketsAcknowledged(rtp_sequence_numbers);
974 }
975}

983
984DataRate RtpVideoSender::CalculateOverheadRate(DataRate data_rate,
985 DataSize packet_size,
986 DataSize overhead_per_packet,
987 Frequency framerate) const {
988 Frequency packet_rate = data_rate / packet_size;
989 if (use_frame_rate_for_overhead_) {
990 framerate = std::max(framerate, Frequency::Hertz(1));
991 DataSize frame_size = data_rate / framerate;
992 int packets_per_frame = ceil(frame_size / packet_size);
993 packet_rate = packets_per_frame * framerate;
994 }
995 return packet_rate.RoundUpTo(Frequency::Hertz(1)) * overhead_per_packet;
996}
